text: Nizhneye Bobino () is a rural locality (a selo) in Maloustyinsky Selsoviet, Mechetlinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 643 as of 2010. There are 8 streets. == Geography == It is located 14 km from Bolsheustyikinskoye, 9 km from Maloustyinskoye. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mechetlinsky District
title: Nizhneye Bobino
